HEADWORD: Superdominant
<hw>Su`per*dom"i*nant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>The sixth tone of the scale; that next above the dominant; --
called also <altname>submediant</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

